The paper discusses the development of a method for achieving transparency in Reinforcement Learning (RL) models, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves generating explanations for the behavior of the RL agent, which can be useful for human users to understand and correct the model. This also relates to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The study also involves a pilot survey to explore user preferences for different explanation properties, which falls under the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The method involves calculating contrasts between the consequences of a policy derived from a user query and the learned policy of the agent, which relates to the sub-category of Robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the development of a format for generating explanations, which falls under the sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL).
